s of dissimulation, whether in affairs of state or affairs of the heart. This beautifully written work crisscrosses Europe, with a special focus on Italy, to explore attitudes toward the art of dissimulation in the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries. Discussing many canonical and lesser-known works, Jon R. Snyder examines the treatment of dissimulation in early modern treatises and writings on the court, civility, moral philosophy, political theory, and in the visual arts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInterpersonal communicationzEuropexHistory. 0aInterpersonal communicationzItalyxHistory. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectszEuropexHistory. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectszItalyxHistory. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectszEuropexHistory. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectszItalyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094444240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944442423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944442/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles